Study hard, get a job, buy a house, get a car, have kids, live with dignity.
Thats the 'Middle Class' dream sold to millions of Indians …. But that dream is cracking real bad.
Middle Class Incomes have largely remained stagnant for a decade - while prices rise. EMIs eat up salaries before the month even begins. You work harder every year, yet feel poorer. Why??

No savings, no safety net just endless hustle. And while the pressure builds quietly in homes across the country, no one in power is listening. How long is this sustainable? 
Is it time to strip away the jumla and look at what’s going wrong ??
